  "notes": "Complete rebuild for corrected Level 3 grapheme set (ay, ee, igh, ow, oo, ar, or, air, ir, ou, oy). All words use ONLY cumulative L1+L2+L3 graphemes. NO consonant clusters (those are unlocked at Level 4). NO graphemes from higher levels: ai/oa (L5), ur/er/ear/ure (L6), split digraphs a-e/i-e/o-e/u-e (L5). Vowel digraphs count as single graphemes, so bark=b+ar+k (CVC), night=n+igh+t (CVC), cheek=ch+ee+k (CVC), shark=sh+ar+k (CVC). The 'oo' grapheme covers both long /oo/ (moon, food) and short /oo/ (book, good). The 'ow' grapheme covers both /ow/ as in cow and /ow/ as in low. Removed words with irregular 'oo' pronunciation (door, poor, moor where oo does not make its regular sound) and words too advanced for age 4-8 (deem, teem, seer, moot, boon, goon, loon). Also removed oar (misleading o+ar decomposition) and ooh (not a standard word)."
